  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 10-20 years in federal prison depending on specific circumstances\n- Longer sentences for more complex or high-value laundering schemes\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the laundered funds\n\n3. Additional potential consequences:\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Criminal record\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, criminal history, and specific federal statutes violated. Prosecutions typically occur under laws like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.",
